---
import BaseLayout from '~/layouts/BaseLayout.astro'

const updated = '2026-06-20'
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy policy — oriz · cards"
  description="What cards.oriz.in collects, what it doesn't, and your rights."
>
  <div class="spine-prose">
    <header class="page-head">
      <p class="eyebrow mono">
        <a href="/">cards</a> / <a href="/legal/">legal</a> / privacy
      </p>
      <h1>privacy policy</h1>
      <p class="meta">Last updated: {updated}</p>
    </header>

    <article class="prose">
      <h2>Who runs this</h2>
      <p>
        cards.oriz.in and the wider <code>oriz.in</code> family are operated
        by Chirag Singhal, based in Bhubaneswar, Odisha, India. Contact:
        <a href="mailto:whyiswhen@gmail.com">whyiswhen@gmail.com</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>What we collect</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Cloudflare Web Analytics</strong> — aggregate page views and
          country. Cookieless. No personal identifiers.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Authentication</strong> — if you sign in, Firebase
          Authentication stores your email, display name, and profile photo
          (if you sign in with Google/GitHub). We never see your password.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Site-specific data</strong> — when you save a card, build a
          comparison, or bookmark a profile, that data is stored in Firestore
          under your user ID and accessible only to you.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Contact form</strong> — submissions go through Web3Forms which
          forwards them to my email. Web3Forms keeps copies; see their privacy
          policy.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>What we don't do</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>No tracking across sessions for analytics (Cloudflare is anonymous).</li>
        <li>No selling of personal data to third parties.</li>
        <li>No newsletters unless you explicitly subscribe.</li>
        <li>No affiliate sign-up steering — card data is published as-is.</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Your rights</h2>
      <p>
        You can delete your account from the <a href="/account/">account
        page</a>; this removes your Firebase Auth record and any saved cards
        / comparisons.
      </p>
      <p>
        Under India's DPDP Act 2023, you have the right to access, correct,
        and delete your personal data. Contact the
        <a href="/legal/grievance/">grievance officer</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>Children</h2>
      <p>
        cards.oriz.in is not directed at children under 13. If you believe a
        child has provided data to us, contact the grievance officer for
        removal.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes</h2>
      <p>
        We will update this page when the practice changes, with the new date
        at the top. Material changes get a banner on the site.
      </p>
    </article>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
